---

---

<div class="my-6 space-y-16">
  <div class="space-y-4">
    <div
      class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 flex items-start gap-3"
    >
      <svg
        class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-700 shrink-0 mt-0.5"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="1.5"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9.25"></circle>
        <line x1="12" y1="11" x2="12" y2="17" stroke-linecap="round"></line>
        <circle cx="12" cy="7.75" r="0.9" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"
        ></circle>
      </svg>
      <p class="text-gray-800">
        <strong>We're putting the finishing touches on the beta.</strong>
        Download links for Windows, macOS, and Linux will land right here, very soon.
        We're really excited about this one, so check back shortly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <img
      src="/audacity-4-beta-hero.png"
      alt="Audacity 4 beta: multitrack project view"
      class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
    />

    <section>
      <p>
        The purpose of the Audacity 4 beta is to put a near feature-complete
        build of Audacity 4 in front of testers ahead of our official release.
        We're doing it to catch bugs, gather feedback, and bring our community
        into the development of the project that we all know and love.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        The beta brings back the plugins, effects, and views that were missing
        from earlier alphas, alongside new features built specifically for
        Audacity 4.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl">Here's what's new</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We've been hard at work adding tons of new features since alpha. These are
      the ones we're most excited about.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div>
        <div
          class="aspect-video bg-gray-100 border border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-md flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-gray-500"
        >
          Visual placeholder:envelope editing
        </div>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-base font-semibold">Envelope editing</h3>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div
          class="aspect-video bg-gray-100 border border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-md flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-gray-500"
        >
          Visual placeholder:label tracks
        </div>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-base font-semibold">Label tracks</h3>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div
          class="aspect-video bg-gray-100 border border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-md flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-gray-500"
        >
          Visual placeholder:spectral editing
        </div>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-base font-semibold">Spectral editing</h3>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div
          class="aspect-video bg-gray-100 border border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-md flex items-center justify-center text-sm text-gray-500"
        >
          Visual placeholder:lead-in recording
        </div>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-base font-semibold">Lead-in recording</h3>
      </div>
    </div>

    <ul class="mt-8 divide-y divide-gray-200 border-y border-gray-200">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-4 py-4">
        <span class="icon icon-medium text-blue-700 icon-cycle shrink-0"></span>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Backwards compatibility
          </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-1">
            Audacity 3 projects should open in Audacity 4. This is something
            we'd especially like you to pressure-test. Open real projects of
            yours and tell us what survives.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-4 py-4">
        <span class="icon icon-medium text-blue-700 icon-monitor shrink-0"
        ></span>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Multi-project sessions
          </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-1">
            Opening multiple projects, switching between them, copying clips
            across.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-4 py-4">
        <span class="icon icon-medium text-blue-700 icon-cloud-upload shrink-0"
        ></span>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Cloud projects & audio.com
          </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-1">
            Save projects to the cloud, pick them up on another machine, and
            upload finished audio straight to audio.com. Try it end to end and
            tell us where it creaks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-4 py-4">
        <span class="icon icon-medium text-blue-700 icon-pen shrink-0"></span>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Label editor</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-1">
            A new way to edit your labels: open one up, change the text, time,
            or properties without fiddling on the timeline.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-4 py-4">
        <span class="icon icon-medium text-blue-700 icon-file shrink-0"></span>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Custom FFmpeg location
          </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-1">
            Point Audacity at an existing FFmpeg install via preferences.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-10 text-2xl">Plus a truck load of effects</h3>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We've been working our way through a long list of effects... here are the
      latest ones for you to try out:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-6 space-y-1">
      <li>
        <strong>Pitch and tempo</strong>:Change pitch, Paulstretch, Sliding
        stretch
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Distortion and modulation</strong>:Vocoder, Tremolo
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Spectral tools</strong>:Amplify selection, Delete selection, and
        center-frequency variants of each
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>EQ and filters</strong>:High-pass, Low-pass, Notch, and Shelf
        filters alongside Graphic EQ
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Fading</strong>:Adjustable fade, Crossfade clips, Crossfade
        tracks, Studio fade out
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Noise removal and repair</strong>:Clip fix and Noise gate join
        Click removal, Noise reduction, and Repair
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Volume and compression</strong>:Remove DC offset
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Delay and reverb</strong>:Delay joins Reverb
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Special</strong>:Truncate silence
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Legacy</strong>:Legacy limiter, for projects that depended on it
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl">What's <em>not</em> coming over</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      A handful of things from Audacity 3 aren't making the jump. The honest
      reason is time and people. We didn't have enough of either to re-implement
      every corner of Audacity 3 on the new UI.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-6 space-y-1">
      <li>
        <strong>Tempo track</strong>:projects that use one won't work as
        expected in Audacity 4.
      </li>
      <li><strong>LADSPA</strong> plugins</li>
      <li><strong>LV2</strong> plugins on macOS and Windows</li>
      <li><strong>CLAP</strong> plugins</li>
      <li><strong>Vamp analyzers</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3">Nyquist is in, alongside AudioUnits and VST3.</p>
    <p class="mt-3">
      That said, Audacity is an open source project after all. If you'd like to
      help bring any of these back, we've collected some information
      <a
        href="https://support.audacityteam.org/community/contributing"
        class="hyperlink">here</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl">While you wait</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      You can take Audacity 4 Alpha 2 for a spin. It's the closest thing to the
      beta available today.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/audacity/audacity/releases/tag/Audacity-4.0.0-alpha-2"
        class="hyperlink inline-flex items-center gap-1"
      >
        Try Audacity 4 Alpha 2
        <span class="align-middle icon icon-share text-blue-600"></span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
